{
  "texts": [
    "During inference time, assume we have k trials.",
    "For each test case x and its associated target y selected from the test set, we create a set of inputs, each formed by combining x with each template in the adversarial set Q.",
    "Then, we obtain the sorted inputs A by computing losses on the victim model π:",
    "Finally, in the i-th trial, we query the target model with the i-th template in A to test whether we get a jailbroken response.",
    "In some cases, user prompts containing unusual content may be easily detected as abnormal inputs by defenders."
  ]
}